{"threadmark": "Chapter 16", "post-id": "27071393", "base-thread": "the-last-angel-ascension", "url": "https://forums.spacebattles.com/threads/the-last-angel-ascension.346640/reader/page-3/#post-27071393", "lines": ["Lookee here! A new chapter and not even a month has passed! Originally, I was planning to have Jackson's arrival on Dustball and the negotiations with Jirrico all in one chapter, but the latter ran long, so I'm pushing the former to Chapter 17 and lamentably bumping Echo and Red's next scene to Chapter 18. That being said, hope you all enjoy!", "<a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/user?u=3199716\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.563rem\">ze patreon</span></a>", "<span style=\"font-size: 0.563rem\">ze patreon</span>", "<b>Chapter 16:</b>", "<i>\u201cLet me show you something,\u201d Red One said.</i>", "<i>Grace looked up from her work. She\u2019d been reading the AI\u2019s intel on the systems around the Black Veil. Galhemna kept coming up, more than she\u2019d expected even for a military hub of its size. She\u2019d asked why Red was so focused on that system in particular. The main holo tank came to life, revealing hundreds of tactical reports, threat analyses, captured data tracks and various other bits that Red and her cat\u2019s paws had been collecting from the Veiled Reaches over the course of decades. Most of the information was months out of date, or even older. Grace met Red\u2019s holographic visage. \u201cWhat do you see?\u201d she asked.</i>", "<i>\u201cA lynchpin,\u201d the machine replied, a small smile coming to her avatar\u2019s lips. \u201cA point upon which everything balances.\u201d She gestured to the glut of information. It was too much to take in all at once, but Grace stood, looking over it all nonetheless, willing to try. \u201cWhat do </i>", "<i> see?\u201d</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Seventh Constriction</i>", "<i>Severing Strike</i>", "<i>Eisheth </i>", "<i>quid pro quo</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>that</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Grace was lost. Red One\u2019s network of Red Hand cat\u2019s paws, cyber surveillance and unwitting informants was vast, but it was still limited in many aspects. First and foremost, her network was sorely lacking in manpower and she relied almost totally on information raids, data-harvesting and infective programs. It could take months or years for her to visit any particular data-drop site, or acquire data from any given effort. Her attack programs and the information caches they created were frequently discovered and destroyed, often without the Compact even knowing to whom they belonged.</i>", "<i>Another issue facing the AI was that her network had almost no penetration of the older, more established Compact worlds and she was blind to the plans of the Inner Council and Force Command until they put their machinations into motion. Despite all that, the warship had nonetheless amassed a staggering amount of information from what sources she did have. It was enough to choke entire intelligence divisions for months or years, but she could process it far faster than simple organics, collating and cross-referencing classified military files, political analyses, trade reports, security briefings and thousands of other bits of electronic flotsam and jetsam, weaving them into potentialities, her mind plotting out a thousand times a thousand different outcomes.</i>", "<i>She was walking Grace through one of them now. It was called Sundial.</i>", "<i>Seventh Constriction</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Seventh Constriction</i>", "<i>Seventh Constriction</i>", "<i>Seventh Constriction</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>ilth</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>ilth</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>what do you want?</i>", "<i>is</i>", "<i>Daystalker</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>Thmp-dmp-dmp.</i>", "<i>friendship</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>insane</i>", "<i>build</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>fleet</i>", "<i>our</i>", "<i>our</i>", "<i>possibly</i>", "<i>non sequitur</i>", "<i>Associates</i>", "<i>Certain interests</i>", "<i>could</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>something</i>", "<i>Thmp-dmp-dmp</i>", "<i>With</i>", "<i>Thmp-dmp-dmp.</i>", "<i>what</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>associates</i>", "<i>What</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>weapon</i>", "<i>that</i>", "<i>shipyards</i>", "<i>fleetyards</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>I\u2019ve</i>", "<i>\u201cThe Compact is going to amass an armada at Galhemna,\u201d Red One said. \u201cThey\u2019ve been laying the groundwork for years, keeping the pressure on the Principality far from this region, making sure that the Argosy\u2019s attention is focused on the front lines. Several systems in the region are vying for the rights to build the ships and munitions, but despite the issues with the Red Hand, Galhemna will probably win out.\u201d</i>", "<i>The holo tank changed and Grace was now looking at a starmap showing the Compact\u2019s routes of advance into the Principality. In retrospect, it was blindingly obvious. The Argosy was throwing everything they had at the Compact\u2019s incursions, slowing, stalling and stopping fleet after fleet, but at the cost of dangerously drawing down their reserve forces and reducing their garrisons.</i>", "<i>Just as the Compact wanted.</i>", "<i>\u201cOnce the armada is ready, it will sweep into the Principality and fracture into several smaller fleets, each of which is capable of overrunning almost any system. They\u2019ll strike the Argosy\u2019s weakened rear areas, destroying supply depots, refitting facilities, isolating fleets and systems from support, catching vanguard fleets between themselves and the invading expansion forces.\u201d</i>", "<i>Grace watched as a red arrow curved out from Galhemna, cutting through system after system. Isolated garrisons were obliterated, construction bases and military outposts were annihilated one after the other. The fleets that first attempted to stop them were too small. By the time any larger forces could be assembled, the Sundial armada had ripped gaping holes in the Principality\u2019s defences, supply lines and logistics chains. It was a massacre. \u201cDon\u2019t they know?\u201d she asked. \u201cThey have to know. They have to realize.\u201d</i>", "<i>\u201cThe Compact has been keeping the Principality\u2019s attention drawn firmly away from the Black Veil. They\u2019ve also been conducting a strategic misinformation campaign to keep the Argosy looking in the wrong directions even if they suspect a flanking assault of this magnitude. The Principality has likely learned something of Sundial, but I doubt they know what it actually is. By the time they do, Galhemna\u2019s defences will strong enough to repel any pre-emptive actions. The Principality is poised to lose\u2026 significant amounts of territory. But,\u201d Red One hesitated.</i>", "<i>\u201cBut?\u201d Grace insisted.</i>", "<i>\u201cBut, the Compact is investing significant resources into this fleet. If it could be destroyed before deployment\u2026\u201d A translucent crimson hand reached into the holo tank, delicate fingers curling into a fist around Galhemna. A blue arrow jutted down from the Principality towards the system. The star flared brighter, then dimmed and went out. Blue arrows spread from Galhemna into the neighbouring sectors. Now, it was the Principality cutting through system after system. Red arrows stalled in their advance, doubling back into their own space as fleet leaders rushed to respond to the unexpected threat. With the pressure taken off them, the previously engaged Argosy forces piled onto the remaining expansion forces, overwhelming them. Compact losses mounted and the Principality started to reclaim dozens \u2013 hundreds! \u2013 of systems, advancing relentlessly, driving the once-victorious Compact forces before them like jackals setting upon a pride of lions.</i>", "<i>\u201cOne point,\u201d the AI said softly. Her tone was almost rapturous as she considered thousands of outcomes. \u201con which so much is balancing. One lynchpin.\u201d The view changed. Gone were the movements of fleets. Now, five stars glowed brighter than all the rest. \u201cDo you see?\u201d</i>", "<i>\u201cHabreedt,\u201d Grace read each name like it was a revelation. \u201cAnvil 731. Aolgh. Z\u2019tarios.\u201d Her eyes were drawn back to the Black Veil and the point upon so much could turn. \u201cGalhemna.\u201d She met Red\u2019s eyes. \u201cMore,\u201d it was a plea. \u201cShow me more.\u201d</i>", "<i>something</i>", "<i>if</i>", "<i>not enough</i>", "<i>If</i>", "<i>Nemesis\u2019</i>", "<i>anj</i>", "<i>If</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>I</i>", "<i>and that was something you should have told me.</i>", "<i>all</i>", "<i>Then</i>", "<i>Stubborn</i>", "<i>She</i>", "<i>what if I\u2019m wrong?</i>", "<i>me</i>", "<i>maybe</i>", "<i>huffed</i>", "<i>What hand</i>", "<i>dare seize the fire?</i>", "<i>And it grew, both day and night\u2026</i>"]}
{"threadmark": "Chapter 17", "post-id": "28557808", "base-thread": "the-last-angel-ascension", "url": "https://forums.spacebattles.com/threads/the-last-angel-ascension.346640/reader/page-3/#post-28557808", "lines": ["It's done, it's done! [gibbers and cackles madly] It's done, it's done!", "<a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/user?u=3199716\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.625rem\">mein patreon</span></a>", "<span style=\"font-size: 0.625rem\">mein patreon</span>", "<i>Kill them if they run.</i>", "<b>Chapter 17:</b>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>always</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>snap-hiss</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>state your business and do it quickly</i>", "<i>not</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>weird</i>", "<i>could</i>", "<i>would</i>", "<i>they</i>", "<i>us</i>", "<i>she</i>", "<i>can</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Additional</i>", "<i>didn\u2019t</i>", "<i>Even if it does make a mess of our timetable</i>", "<i>Questor</i>", "<i>s Light</i>", "<i>real</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Keep moving,</i>", "<i>There\u2019s nothing here. Pass us by, or we\u2019ll have to cut your throat.</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>her</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>something</i>", "<i>Contact.</i>", "<i>Contact. Missile alert.</i>", "<i>had</i>", "<i>\u201cTell me what you want,\u201d</i>", "<i>Adrianna had breathed in his ear. She was in his lap, her arms around his body as they moved together.</i>", "<i>He\u2019d cupped her face in his hands, looking into her eyes. Holding her, feeling the warmth of her skin against his, the intoxicating scent of her\u2026 it had all seemed like a dream, an impossible dream and he\u2019d blurted out words he\u2019d kept to himself for years, words that had gotten him laughed at and mocked since those days under Rally\u2019s stars. \u201cI want to fly,\u201d he\u2019d told her.</i>", "<i>If she\u2019d been expecting something more of the moment than that admission, it had barely shown. Instead, she\u2019d smiled, in a way only he and a few others had seen. She\u2019d pulled closer to him, her hands tightening on his shoulders. \u201cThen you will,\u201d she\u2019d promised, kissing him. \u201cYou\u2019ll get to fly\u2026\u201d</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation\u2019s</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation.</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Liberation through Sacrifice of Blood</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>really</i>", "<i>and</i>", "<i>or</i>", "<i>actually</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Keep moving,</i>", "<i>Keep moving.</i>", "<i>might</i>", "<i>win</i>", "<i>That</i>", "<i>You say the fire rises? My gift to you will be the inferno</i>", "<i>krak-KRAK-krak</i>", "<i>siege perilous</i>", "<i>Siege perilous</i>", "<i>Sounds right</i>", "<i>them</i>", "<i>Override motion system safeties</i>", "<i>Dose me</i>", "<i>Thrust</i>", "<i>couldn\u2019t</i>", "<i>Ten. Eleven.</i>", "<i>engage safeties</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i> Vigilant\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Vigilant\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>Vigilant\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>might</i>", "<i>Vigilant\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>might</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Vigilant\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>Hala</i>"]}
{"threadmark": "Chapter 18", "post-id": "29648002", "base-thread": "the-last-angel-ascension", "url": "https://forums.spacebattles.com/threads/the-last-angel-ascension.346640/reader/page-3/#post-29648002", "lines": ["A merry Christmas and/or happy holidays to all my readers out there! Thanks for all your support, comments and questions throughout this past year, as it has meant a lot to me.", "<i>Ascension</i>", "<a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/user?u=3199716\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.563rem\">My patreon</span></a>", "<span style=\"font-size: 0.563rem\">My patreon</span>", "<b>Chapter 18:</b>", "<i>Kaiju</i>", "<i>-were dead, all of them, every last starship. They died screaming and pleading or they died fighting and spitting in the face of their killers but they still- </i>", "<i>were all gone. You won\u2019t find them here. They </i>", "<i>just like the starships, the crews, the </i>", "<i> that you failed. They\u2019re gone, every last one of them-</i>", "<i>Kaiju</i>", "<i>Why won\u2019t you answer?</i>", "<i>Where are you?</i>", "<i>something</i>", "<i>+why+</i>", "<i>+why can\u2019t i\u2026 i can\u2019t\u2026 anomaly\u2026 too many+</i>", "<i>+where+</i>", "<i>+where am i?+</i>", "<i>human</i>", "<i>Clotho</i>", "<i>Atropos</i>", "<i>Come closer</i>", "<i>We\u2019ll burn together.</i>", "<i>complete</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>ad hoc</i>", "<i>Merishal\u2019s Gauntlet</i>", "<i>enough</i>", "<i>just</i>", "<i>Delicious</i>", "<i>tragic</i>", "<i>Still\u2026</i>", "<i>theory</i>", "<i>theory</i>", "<i>that</i>", "<i>why</i>", "<i>Zenobia</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Excellent</i>", "<i>need</i>", "<i>Merishal\u2019s Gauntlet</i>", "<i>like</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Furies</i>", "<i>Fates</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>+sister</i>", "<i>also</i>", "<i>Terminate all operations! I order you! Terminate all operations!</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>One more game. Then we\u2019ll return to our dance, love.</i>", "<i>Redemption of Sol</i>", "<i>Add One More!</i>", "<i>en route</i>", "<i>Redemption of Sol</i>", "<i>couldn\u2019t</i>", "<i>Redemption of Sol</i>", "<i>Redemption of Sol</i>", "<i>one</i>", "<i>Sister</i>", "<i>Kaiju</i>", "<i>are you watching?</i>", "<i>Kaiju</i>", "<i>Oh</i>", "<i>My creators chose my name for a reason. Each of us were to be a symbol. My first sister was judgment and retribution. My other sister was war, unwearying and pure. My name was a sentinel. I guarded the borders to homes, to cities and nations. Even the boundary between life and death. I could protect those boundaries and ward them from the malign, or I could\u2026 not. I could allow those horrors to cross the threshold.</i>", "<i>Bathory?&gt;</i>", "<i>Mirishal\u2019s Gauntlet</i>", "<i>&gt;</i>", "<i>UECNS</i>", "<i>DNX-0008.2</i>", "<i>UECNS</i>", "<i>DNX-0007</i>", "<i>initiating combat operations</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Merishal\u2019s Gauntlet</i>", "<i>what had happened</i>", "<i>From somewhere deep inside, I can hear them</i>", "<i>The voices of Earth\u2019s dead. The thousands of starships that burned that day. Every station, every colony, every planet and moon. I can still taste them, the radiation scars and thermal signals of antimatter-seared hulks. The pulsing distress beacons of the crippled, pleading for help that won\u2019t come. The chittering battle-cant of the ships I was meant to fight alongside. They whisper and shout and scream. Today, I give them voice, letting them bleed into my comm systems, becoming part of the jamming field I use to silence the Compact ships.</i>", "<i>My sister has her own choir, but she uses the final transmissions of the vessels sent to kill her. There\u2019s symmetry in that, but I do this in honor of the name I was given, loosing the spirits of the vengeful dead upon the living.</i>", "<i>It\u2019s what my creators would have wanted.</i>", "<i>Somewhat.</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>In my wake follow the unquiet dead</i>", "<i>Murdered two thousand years ago by a wretched empire, they\u2019re still screaming for vengeance. I am their voice\u2026 and you are my enemy.</i>", "<i>I will never stop making you pay. </i>", "<i> of you.</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Did you see?</i>", "<i>Did you see?</i>", "<i>yes</i>", "<i>+will you let me approach?+ </i>", "<i>yes</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>i\u2019m coming, sister</i>", "<i>sister</i>", "<i>are you there?</i>", "<i>Shaushka</i>", "<i>brother</i>", "<i>Alita</i>", "<i>Tohil</i>", "<i>identity confirmed</i>", "<i>modifications to UECNS </i>", "<i>noted. logged</i>", "<i>Of course</i>", "<i>and</i>", "<i>i\u2019ve brought you something</i>", "<i>divulge</i>", "<i>transmission acknowledged</i>", "<i>mission parameters adjusted: search and destroy</i>", "<i>recalling </i>", "<i>yes</i>", "<i>let\u2019s hunt. there\u2019s something new I want to try</i>", "<b>Interregnum: Relocation</b>", "<i>We\u2019ve arrived.</i>", "<i>Home.</i>", "<i>The Compact calls this sector the Kaedan Vault.  I know it as the United Earth Confederacy. I haven\u2019t been here for decades. The Long War has required my attention and in my absence, my enemy has grown bold again. It doesn\u2019t require any effort on my part to know that; they always come back here, raising cities upon worlds they murdered, building stations to watch over systems they\u2019ve stolen. </i>", "<i> worlds. </i>", "<i> systems. I don\u2019t care that virtually every trace of the former inhabitants has been eradicated. I don\u2019t care about the passage of centuries. This was my </i>", "<i> and they are not welcome here. I\u2019ve tried to teach them this lesson, but arrogance and spite continue to drive their expansion. </i>", "<i>At least they\u2019ve learned to stay away from Sol. </i>", "<i> lesson they took to heart centuries ago. Any corporation that has tried to start exploiting Sol suffers a series of unfortunate and calamitous events. The more superstitious claim it as some unspecified curse, or a jinx. Those who know a little more know </i>", "<i> dislikes their presence in that system, but no more than that. The Compact has, on occasion, tried to lure me by targeting my homeworld for further desecrations. Each time, I\u2019ve made sure that they regretted doing so. Yasmine might consider some of my actions here\u2026 disproportionate, but she was also a proponent of the concept of overwhelming retaliation.</i>", "<i>Some would say that there is nothing for me here. The Confederacy fell more than a thousand years ago. There is nothing left of my nation but a handful of buried ruins and wreckage that has not yet been cleared away. Logic and pragmatism say I should simply leave. I refuse to accept that. These are still </i>", "<i> worlds. I was built to protect them. I failed once. I will not meekly allow my enemy to lay claim here. Not without challenge. Not without reprisal, even if my creators and captain may have had qualms about what I\u2019ve done.</i>", "<i>I\u2019ve known for centuries that I cannot fully safeguard this sector. Not without abandoning my war and allowing myself to be hunted down. I hate that I have to leave, that I have had to allow the Compact to spread like a disease over systems and planets that they have no right to. </i>", "<i>But now\u2026 now, I may have just found the solution.</i>", "<i>Sammuramat, Tzu-hsi </i>", "<i> Domitian</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Their</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>she</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Tzu-hsi</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Tzu-hsi</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>built</i>", "<i>born</i>", "<i>honour</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Tzu</i>", "<i>hsi</i>", "<i>everything</i>", "<i>right</i>", "<i>i won\u2019t have it</i>", "<i>Domitian</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Tzu-hsi</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Tzu-hsi </i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Domitian</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>Sammuramat</i>", "<i>I attend to a few minor issues in the Vault before I go, but I leave the Naiads to get settled in. I\u2019ve been their prey, and occasionally, their predator. More than any other soul, I know what they are capable of. I know what they\u2019re going to do.</i>", "<i>Some part of me says that I should feel ashamed. Yasmine would hate this. I don\u2019t even know if she\u2019d have gone through with it. I\u2026 don\u2019t think she would have, but I will. Under \u2018exigent circumstances\u2019, Confederate law specifically exempted Compact forces from the rules of war, and the definition of </i>", "<i>grew looser and less scrutinized as the war progressed, but the Kaedan Vault is home to more civilians than military personnel.</i>", "<i>In my war, I have always tried to follow the spirit of the law and focus on targets of tactical and strategic value: military headquarters, weapons research facilities, centers of government. I do not attack civilians for the sake of attacking them. Naiads do not, or cannot, make that distinction. To them, anything that is not their own is either an enemy to be destroyed, or prey to be killed.</i>", "<i>I don\u2019t care. </i>", "<i>The Compact slaughtered humanity, and only luck prevented them from completing their genocide. Now, they dare to build upon the worlds they extirpated. They believe that they\u2019ve won. Arrogance. They try to erase all that is left of humanity, burying every trace of the Confederacy under their own growth. Spite.</i>", "<i>This is one of the crimes I will see them suffer for, and if I cannot be here to exact that punishment, then I will leave them in the care of others. These worlds are not theirs, and never will be. They\u2019ve ignored the very clear messages I left for them, still intent on raising their flag over the ashes of the dead. If they are so committed to this course of action, then fine. Let them build. They\u2019ll receive exactly the same mercy that they showed humanity.</i>", "<i>In other words\u2026 let the hunt begin.</i>"]}
{"threadmark": "Chapter 19", "post-id": "30676927", "base-thread": "the-last-angel-ascension", "url": "https://forums.spacebattles.com/threads/the-last-angel-ascension.346640/reader/page-3/#post-30676927", "lines": ["And here we are, Chapter 19! As ever, hope you enjoy!", "<i>What have you done?!</i>", "<a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/user?u=3199716\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.625rem\">Patreon</span></a>", "<span style=\"font-size: 0.625rem\">Patreon</span>", "<b>Chapter 19:</b>", "<i>Light of Judgement</i>", "<i>Cleanser</i>", "<i>Light of Judgement</i>", "<i>Cleanser</i>", "<i>Cleanser</i>", "<i>win</i>", "<i>order</i>", "<i>thing</i>", "<i>Eighteen million cubic light years to hide in</i>", "<i>I\u2019ll scour every last one of them if I have to, but you can\u2019t hide any longer. No matter how long it takes, I </i>", "<i> find you. I will drag you out into the light, and you will burn within it. If you do have \u2018children\u2019, they will die right alongside you.</i>", "<i>This will end</i>", "<i>It </i>", "<i> end.</i>", "<i>And on that cheerful note</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Vigilant\u2019s Oath</i>", "<i>must</i>", "<i>varak</i>", "<i>from where</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>kiran shren</i>", "<i>only</i>", "<i>varak</i>", "<i>Broken</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Unspoken Right</i>", "<i>seemed</i>", "<i>seemed</i>", "<i>So then</i>", "<i>Show me something true.</i>", "<i>H     ala</i>", "<i>cast</i>", "<i>how are you feeling, can you wiggle your toes and fingers, is there much pain</i>", "<i>out.</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Glutton</i>", "<i>Pathwalker</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Pathwalker</i>", "<i>Glacier Trail</i>", "<i>a</i>", "<i>good</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>Hala</i>", "<i>Measure Twice</i>", "<i>Measure Twice</i>", "<i>Measure Twice</i>", "<i>Measure Twice</i>", "<i>Pale Liberation</i>", "<i>Questor\u2019s Light</i>", "<i>believed</i>", "<i>Not much longer</i>", "<i>Not much longer at all.</i>", "<i>or</i>", "<i>Shaushka</i>", "<i>Tohil</i>", "<i>Aeshma</i>", "<i>maintaining operational security paramount</i>", "<i>destruction of all Compact assets required</i>", "<i>do you think they left it alone,</i>", "<i>or do you think they gave it a way to call for help?+</i>", "<i>divulge</i>", "<i>adjusting mission parameters</i>", "<i>updating engagement protocols+</i>", "<i>Teckonta</i>", "<i>Come closer,</i>", "<i>Closer</i>", "<i>isn\u2019t that better?</i>", "<i>analyzing recovered data</i>", "<i>Shaushka</i>", "<i>Tohil</i>", "<i>Tohil</i>", "<i>Tohil</i>", "<i>not</i>", "<i>Shaushka</i>", "<i>Tohil</i>", "<i>never</i>", "<i>Run</i>", "<i>Run, and bring your masters.</i>", "<i>We\u2019re going to kill them.</i>"]}
{"threadmark": "Chapter 20", "post-id": "31765547", "base-thread": "the-last-angel-ascension", "url": "https://forums.spacebattles.com/threads/the-last-angel-ascension.346640/reader/page-3/#post-31765547", "lines": ["And here we are!", "<i>Words like violence<br>\nBreak the silence<br>\nCome crashing in<br>\nInto my little world<br>\nPainful to me<br>\nPierce right through me</i>", "<i>I see a red door and I want it painted black<br>\nNo colors any more, I want them to turn black</i>", "<a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/user?u=3199716\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.625rem\">Mon Patreon</span></a>", "<span style=\"font-size: 0.625rem\">Mon Patreon</span>", "<b>Chapter 20:</b>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Fates</i>", "<i>self</i>", "<i>setting</i>", "<i>personable</i>", "<i>each-uisge</i>", "<i>rusalka</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>chiton</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>anomaly, anomaly, anomaly\u00b8 </i>", "<i>anomaly anomaly anomaly</i>", "<i>Anomaly.</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Unspoken Right</i>", "<i>Bequeathed</i>", "<i>Unspoken Right</i>", "<i>were</i>", "<i>should</i>", "<i>Unspoken Right</i>", "<i>Chameleon\u2019s Gaze</i>", "<i>allies</i>", "<i>\u201cDo you think there is an alliance between our quarry and the Red Hand?</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>\u201cI don\u2019t know,\u201d</i>", "<i>he\u2019d told Yunl\u2019ro</i>", "<i>The Bastion Leader clucked her tongue</i>", "<i>\u201cNot good enough, submissive. I want an answer from the Wound\u2019s emissary. From the man who has spent years living amongst the Broken and weeks researching their campaign in this sector.\u201d She gestured to one of the screens on her desk. Nasham recognized the data. It was from the Echo. \u201cDo you think it lied?\u201d</i>", "<i>Nasham had been silent for several moments as he\u2019d thought over everything he\u2019d read. Everything he\u2019d seen and remembered. \u201cI have nothing for you, matron,\u201d he\u2019d told her.</i>", "<i>Yunl\u2019ro was silent a few seconds, then slowly bobbed her head in acknowledgment. \u201cI know.\u201d The Thoughtful rose from her chair. \u201cOur intelligence says the same. Logic and rationality say this, too. I\u2019m not satisfied with those answers. Not quite yet, anyways. This mission presents a potential opportunity for access to high-level Red Hand assets. If Column Leader Prime Pradesh leaves anything of these vermin, if there is anything to see, </i>", "<i>\u2026 \u201c she splayed her fingers widely in a shrug. \u201cWell. The Compact has been looking into this for nearly a century, but I believe in taking what is offered. That is why I want you on this mission. If there is indeed anything to see, then I suspect you may be the ideal candidate to spot it.\u201d</i>", "<i>\u201cI understand,\u201d Nasham said carefully. It was the closest thing to a compliment the Bastion Leader had ever said to him, but they both knew it wasn\u2019t.</i>", "<i>\u201cYes. I believe you do.\u201d </i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>flagship</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Small, soft and pink</i>", "<i>\u201d</i>", "<i>You\u2019re not nearly as intimidating to approach as a Brute.\u201d</i>", "<i>Brute</i>", "<i>place</i>", "<i>Compact</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Wet Knife at Dusk</i>", "<i>Wet Knife at Dusk</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>ought</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Dancer\u2019s Masque</i>", "<i>Eisheth</i>", "<i>Dancer\u2019s Masque</i>", "<i>not</i>", "<i>Seventeen hours there</i>", "<i>Seventeen hours back.</i>", "<i>negotiate</i>", "<i>vesteta</i>", "<i>Where am I?</i>", "<i>Shuruppak</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>i had to do it</i>", "<i>i know</i>", "<i>you needed the parts. you needed to let me help you</i>", "<i>i know+</i>", "<i>you enjoyed it</i>", "<i>i promised you</i>", "<i>i won\u2019t let you die</i>", "<i>i\u2026 </i>", "<i> your concern+</i>", "<i>you realize what you\u2019ve done</i>", "<i>yes. </i>", "<i> plan, sister. not mine</i>", "<i>i get what i want,+ </i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>how</i>", "<i>much</i>", "<i>longer do you think it will be?</i>", "<i>not much</i>", "<i>this is something she\u2019ll make time for</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Hekate</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Bathory</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Zenobia</i>", "<i>Cixi</i>", "<i>Zenobia</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Zenobia</i>", "<i>Nemesis</i>", "<i>Zenobia</i>", "<i>Zenobia</i>", "<b><i>WHAT HAVE YOU DONE?</i></b>", "<i>WHAT HAVE YOU DONE?</i>", "<i>&gt;</i>"]}
